         <abstract>
            <p>Some algorithms are introduced, whereby a function defined on an arbitrarily spaced set of abscissas may be interpolated or approximated by trigonometric or hyperbolic polynomials. The interpolation may be ordinary or osculatory. Least squares approximation is included; the approximant may be a pure sine series or a cosine series or a balanced trigonometric or hyperbolic polynomial. An application to a periodicity-search is described.</p>
          </abstract>
